<subSubSection lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="331" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,744,1751,1815]" box="[151,325,1788,1815]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,246,1788,1814]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1748,1772]" captionTargetBox="[165,1425,197,1713]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[151,1436,181,1725]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 14. Molopopterus hastata. a. abdominal apodemes 2S; b. genital capsule; c. subgenital plate, style, connective and sternite IX; d. subgenital plate, dorsal view; e. style, dorsal view; f. connective; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413895/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">Figs 14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[258,286,1788,1815]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="46.[151,250,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[170,1420,195,1846]" captionTargetId="figure-24@46.[154,1433,181,1857]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 26. a–d. Lublinia acaciae; e–h. Lublinia anchoroides; i–l. Molopopterus hastata; m–p. Molopopterus parajota; q–t. Molopopterus steeleae; u–x. Molopopterus ugandica." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413921/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">26</figureCitation>
i–l)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,1860,2030]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1860,1886]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">Description.</emphasis>
Body lemon yellow (specimen preserved in ethanol before examination). Apical area of vertex, central area of pronotum and brochosome field of forewing slightly darkened; eyes grey; tip of anteclypeus dark brown; basal triangles of mesonotum brown, long. (
<figureCitation box="[644,729,1932,1959]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="46.[151,250,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[170,1420,195,1846]" captionTargetId="figure-24@46.[154,1433,181,1857]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 26. a–d. Lublinia acaciae; e–h. Lublinia anchoroides; i–l. Molopopterus hastata; m–p. Molopopterus parajota; q–t. Molopopterus steeleae; u–x. Molopopterus ugandica." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413921/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">Figs 26</figureCitation>
i–l)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,1860,2030]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">
Male abdominal apodemes 2S (
<figureCitation box="[553,647,1968,1994]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1748,1772]" captionTargetBox="[165,1425,197,1713]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[151,1436,181,1725]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 14. Molopopterus hastata. a. abdominal apodemes 2S; b. genital capsule; c. subgenital plate, style, connective and sternite IX; d. subgenital plate, dorsal view; e. style, dorsal view; f. connective; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413895/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">Fig. 14a</figureCitation>
) extended to middle of sternite IV. Anal tube (
<figureCitation box="[1169,1264,1968,1995]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1748,1772]" captionTargetBox="[165,1425,197,1713]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[151,1436,181,1725]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 14. Molopopterus hastata. a. abdominal apodemes 2S; b. genital capsule; c. subgenital plate, style, connective and sternite IX; d. subgenital plate, dorsal view; e. style, dorsal view; f. connective; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413895/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">Fig. 14b</figureCitation>
) far surpassing hind margin of pygofer lobe.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413895" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4413895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413895/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="330" startId="29.[151,250,1748,1772]" targetBox="[165,1425,197,1713]" targetPageId="29">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1748,1845]" pageId="29" pageNumber="330">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,289,1748,1773]" pageId="29" pageNumber="330">FIGURE 14.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cao &amp; Dietrich &amp; Dmitriev &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2020" box="[297,522,1749,1773]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Molopopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="330" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hastata">
<emphasis box="[297,522,1749,1773]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="330">Molopopterus hastata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. a. abdominal apodemes 2S; b. genital capsule; c. subgenital plate, style, connective and sternite IX; d. subgenital plate, dorsal view; e. style, dorsal view; f. connective; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, ventral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1891,2025]" lastBlockId="30.[151,1436,151,573]" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="331" pageId="29" pageNumber="330">
Pygofer lobe (
<figureCitation box="[366,464,1891,1918]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1748,1772]" captionTargetBox="[165,1425,197,1713]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[151,1436,181,1725]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 14. Molopopterus hastata. a. abdominal apodemes 2S; b. genital capsule; c. subgenital plate, style, connective and sternite IX; d. subgenital plate, dorsal view; e. style, dorsal view; f. connective; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413895/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="330">Fig. 14b</figureCitation>
) with distal angle somewhat blunt, with relatively dense fine setae and microsetae. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[349,478,1927,1954]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1748,1772]" captionTargetBox="[165,1425,197,1713]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[151,1436,181,1725]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 14. Molopopterus hastata. a. abdominal apodemes 2S; b. genital capsule; c. subgenital plate, style, connective and sternite IX; d. subgenital plate, dorsal view; e. style, dorsal view; f. connective; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413895/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="330">Figs 14b, d</figureCitation>
) with about 3 macrosetae, marginal setae numerous, differentiated into three groups: basal group long and thick; middle group peg-like, from subbase to subapex; apical group rigid, relatively long and sparse. Style (
<figureCitation box="[305,398,1999,2025]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1748,1772]" captionTargetBox="[165,1425,197,1713]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[151,1436,181,1725]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 14. Molopopterus hastata. a. abdominal apodemes 2S; b. genital capsule; c. subgenital plate, style, connective and sternite IX; d. subgenital plate, dorsal view; e. style, dorsal view; f. connective; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413895/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="330">Fig. 14e</figureCitation>
) with apical part robust, with transverse whorl-like sculptures; preapical lobe relatively small, with row of sensory setae above preapical lobe. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[841,932,151,178]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1748,1772]" captionTargetBox="[165,1425,197,1713]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[151,1436,181,1725]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 14. Molopopterus hastata. a. abdominal apodemes 2S; b. genital capsule; c. subgenital plate, style, connective and sternite IX; d. subgenital plate, dorsal view; e. style, dorsal view; f. connective; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413895/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="331">Fig. 14f</figureCitation>
) with manubrium very wide. Aedeagal shaft (
<figureCitation box="[159,284,187,214]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1748,1772]" captionTargetBox="[165,1425,197,1713]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[151,1436,181,1725]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 14. Molopopterus hastata. a. abdominal apodemes 2S; b. genital capsule; c. subgenital plate, style, connective and sternite IX; d. subgenital plate, dorsal view; e. style, dorsal view; f. connective; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413895/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="331">
Figs 
<quantity box="[214,259,187,213]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.4" pageId="30" pageNumber="331" unit="g" value="14.0">14g</quantity>
, h
</figureCitation>
) thin and long, slightly curved, apex acuminate, with pair of thin processes subapically on dorsal margin directed basad and close to shaft; dorsal apodeme slightly expanded dorsad; preatrium and dorsal apodeme closely appressed, cleft narrow; gonopore subapical on dorsal side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,151,573]" box="[199,619,295,321]" pageId="30" pageNumber="331">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,371,295,321]" pageId="30" pageNumber="331">Measurement.</emphasis>
Male length 
<quantity box="[519,616,295,321]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="30" pageNumber="331" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.90mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
